#note I realized after I hit my clock that ULU had to be the right move (I had considered it for a minute) - the bag is really heavy on consonants (18/54 remaining tiles are vowels). the only advantage of my play is that both blanks are unseen, but here AAINS and ALS bingo the same amount next turn. a lesson not to make a play on auto-pilot!
